Flar Oldbottles Nets, Ropes, Cables, Hawsers, and Cords was a warehouse and a shop in the 14 century DR.
Flar Oldbottles Nets and a shop attached to its northern wall, a small shack called Jumbles Fresh Fish, was located on the eastern side of the canal that connected the Basin with the Dragonmere lake on the southern side of Suzail. It stood to the northwest of Silverscales Street. In an alley between Flar Oldbottles Nets and its southern neighborâ€“Red Sunsets Trading Company warehouse, was hidden Jusks Stroll, a gate-link that functioned exclusively under cover of the night and connected this alley with the alley behind Dragons Jaws tavern.
Flar Oldbottles warehouse was a thick, long, two-storied building with a hammerbeam wooden loft and slate roof perched atop.
Flar Oldbottles Nets, Ropes, Cables, Hawsers, and Cords once belonged to a wealthy hin investor from Suzail named Imprur Jusk, sometime before the late 14 century DR. The halfling was the person who discovered Jusks Stroll gate hidden behind his warehouse.
